{
  "texts": [
    "One uses Yao garbled circuits (GC) [106].",
    "In GC, the circuit garbler generates the garbled circuit and gives it to the other party who evaluates it.",
    "The circuit evaluator obtains the other party's inputs using oblivious transfer (OT) before evaluating the circuit, and the rest of the evaluation is non-interactive.",
    "The circuit evaluator then reveals the values at the output gate to the other party.",
    "In GC, fresh circuits must be used each time the computation is run.A second regime uses secret-sharing, as exemplified by the GMW protocol [51]."
  ]
}